functions.name: ABS
functions.description:
ABS
Returns the absolute value of a number.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The number of which to return the absolute value.

returns.description: the absolute value of the `value` parameter

functions.name: ACOS
functions.description:
ACOS
Returns the inverse cosine of a value, in radians.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value for which to calculate the inverse cosine. Must be between -1 and 1, inclusive.

functions.name: ACOSH
functions.description:
ACOSH
Returns the inverse hyperbolic cosine of a number.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value for which to calculate the inverse hyperbolic cosine. Must be greater than or equal to 1.

functions.name: AND
functions.description:
AND
Returns true if all of the provided arguments are logically true, and false if any of the provided arguments are logically false.

parameters.name: var_args_expressions
parameters.description: An expression or reference that represents some logical value, i.e. TRUE or FALSE, or an expression that can be converted to a logical value.

functions.name: AVERAGE
functions.description:
AVERAGE
Returns the numerical average value in a dataset, ignoring text.

parameters.name: var_args_values
parameters.description: values to use when calculating the average value.

functions.name: CEILING
functions.description:
CEILING
Rounds a number up to the nearest integer multiple of specified significance.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value to round up to the nearest integer multiple of factor.

parameters.name: factor
parameters.description: The number to whose multiples value will be rounded.

functions.name: CHAR
functions.description:
CHAR
Convert a number into a character according to the current Unicode table.

parameters.name: number
parameters.description: The number of the character to look up from the current Unicode table in decimal format.

functions.name: CLEAN
functions.description:
CLEAN
Returns the text with the non-printable ASCII characters removed.

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: The text whose non-printable characters are to be removed.

functions.name: COALESCE
functions.description:
COALESCE
Returns the first parameter whose value exists

parameters.name: parameters
parameters.description: The value to return if it exists

functions.name: CODE
functions.description:
CODE
Returns the numeric Unicode map value of the first character in the string provided.

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: The string whose first character's Unicode map value will be returned.

functions.name: CONCATENATE
functions.description:
CONCATENATE
Returns the concatenation of multiple values.
examples:
// returns This is a sentence.
CONCATENATE("This ", "is ", "a ", "sentence.")

functions.name: COS
functions.description:
COS
Returns the cosine of a value, in radians.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value for which to calculate the cosine. Must be between -1 and 1, inclusive.

functions.name: COSH
functions.description:
COSH
Returns the hyperbolic cosine of a number.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The real number for which to calculate the hyperbolic cosine.

functions.name: COUNT
functions.description:
COUNT
Returns a count of the number of numeric values in a dataset.

parameters.name: var_args_values
parameters.description: Value to include in the count.

functions.name: COUNTA
functions.description:
COUNTA
Returns a count of the number of values in a dataset.

functions.name: COUNTBLANK
functions.description:
COUNTBLANK
Returns the number of blank values in a dataset.

functions.name: DATE
functions.description:
DATE
Converts a provided year, month, and day into a date.

functions.name: DATEVALUE
functions.description:
DATEVALUE
Converts a provided date string in a known format to a date value.

functions.name: DAY
functions.description:
DAY
Returns the day of the month that a specific date falls on, in numeric format.

functions.name: DAYS360
functions.description:
DAYS360
Returns the difference between two days based on the 360 day year used in some financial interest calculations.

functions.name: DEGREES
functions.description:
DEGREES
Converts an angle value in radians to degrees.

functions.name: DOLLAR
functions.description:
DOLLAR
Formats a number into the locale-specific currency format.

functions.name: EVEN
functions.description:
EVEN
Returns number rounded up to the nearest even integer.

functions.name: EXACT
functions.description:
EXACT
Tests whether two strings are identical.

functions.name: EXP
functions.description:
EXP
Returns Euler's number, e (~2.718) raised to a power.

functions.name: FACT
functions.description:
FACT
Returns the factorial of a number.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value for which to calculate the factorial.

functions.name: FACTDOUBLE
functions.description:
FACTDOUBLE
Returns the double factorial of a number.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value for which to calculate the double factorial.

functions.name: FIND
functions.description:
FIND
Returns the position at which a string is first found within text, case-sensitive.

parameters.name: text_to_search
parameters.description: Text to search for the first instance of `search_for`.

parameters.name: starting_at
parameters.description: argument Position index to begin the search.

functions.name: FIXED
functions.description:
FIXED
Formats a number with a fixed number of decimal places.

parameters.name: number_of_places
parameters.description: Number of decimal places to display in the result.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: Whether or not to suppress the thousands separator.

functions.name: FLOOR
functions.description:
FLOOR
Rounds a number down to the nearest integer multiple of specified significance.

parameters.name: significance
parameters.description: The number to whose multiples `value` will be rounded.

functions.name: GCD
functions.description:
GCD
Returns the greatest common divisor of one or more integers.

parameters.name: var_args_values
parameters.description: Value to consider to calculate greatest common divisor.

functions.name: INT
functions.description:
INT
Rounds a number down to the nearest integer that is less than or equal to it.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: Value to round down to the nearest integer.

functions.name: ISBLANK
functions.description:
ISBLANK
Checks whether the field's value is empty.

functions.name: LATITUDE
functions.description:
LATITUDE
Returns the latitude of the current feature (record or repeatable item)

functions.name: LONGITUDE
functions.description:
LONGITUDE
Returns the longitude of the current feature (record or repeatable item)

functions.name: REPEATABLEVALUES
functions.description:
REPEATABLEVALUES
Return a specific field from multiple repeatable items

parameters.name: repeatableDataName
parameters.description: The data name of the repeatable field for `repeatableVariable`

parameters.name: dataName
parameters.description: The data name of the field to extract from each repeatable item

returns.description: An array of values of the `dataName` field from each item

functions.name: REPEATABLESUM
functions.description:
REPEATABLESUM
Return the sum of a specific numeric field across multiple repeatable items

parameters.name: repeatableDataName
parameters.description: The data name of the repeatable field for `repeatableVariable`

parameters.name: dataName
parameters.description: The data name of the field to extract from each repeatable item

returns.description: The sum of the `dataName` field within each repeatable item

functions.name: SINH
functions.description:
SINH
Returns the hyperbolic sine of a number

functions.name: STATUS
functions.description:
STATUS
Returns the current record status

functions.name: VERSIONINFO
functions.description:
VERSIONINFO
Returns version information about the app.
examples:
// returns Apple iPhone6,2 iOS 8.1 Fulcrum 2.7.0 2162
VERSIONINFO()

functions.name: X_ISNEW
functions.description:
X_ISNEW
Returns a boolean indicating whether the current feature (record or repeatable item) is new. It returns false if it's being updated.

functions.name: X_ISUPDATE
functions.description:
X_ISUPDATE
Returns a boolean indicating whether the current feature (record or repeatable item) is being updated. It returns false if it's a new record.
